BigL80
5.0 out of 5 starsThis Isn't For Anyone Who Liked Drake Post Take Care
July 4, 2018
Format: MP3 MusicVerified Purchase
Since Take Care, there has been two types of Drake "fans":

A: people that were with him since the very beginning (Room For Improvement and the Heartbreak Drake series) and know that singing has always been apart of his platform just as much as rapping.

B: people that joined Drake's wave at Take Care and think his singing is just a tacked on feature of his work and expect everything he does to be mostly rap.

In this newest album, drake tries to give both types of fans exactly what they expect, and because he did that, one group (the post Take Care "fans") feels like this project is mostly filler (all of Side B and some songs on Side A). Both sides, however, have so much content to offer. Nonstop, Emotionless, Sandra's Rose, Ratchet Happy Birthday, Don't Matter to Me, Final Fantasy...it is very possible to enjoy this album without even listening to the two singles. Day-1 fans will appreciate this whole project and I highly recommend it for anyone that is one.

Other albums I currently listen to: Beautiful Thugger Girls, Daytona, KOD, Invasion of Privacy, The Beautiful & Damned

Droo Beam
4.0 out of 5 starsAn album that deserves to be played from start to finish.
July 4, 2018
Format: MP3 MusicVerified Purchase
A solid 4 and half out of 5. After hearing the minimalist approach to "Im Upset", i hoped the album had more of this kind of production. The stripped down and bare bone beats fit like a glove. I haven't bought an album in a long while and the last rap album i bought was Jay Z's Blueprint vol 3. I wasn't really a fan of Drake until the joint he did with 21. Don't take anyone's word for this album, especially the negative reviews such as the highly contradictory critique by Melon Drop, it's not anywhere as bad as he says. The 1983 MJ sample he uses is perfect as well as the Mariah Carey sample, both will get stuck in your head upon first listen. The first disc is quite raw and the second is more alternative and experimental in a good way. The album has a high replay value, which is the highest praise i can give an album.

Format: MP3 MusicVerified Purchase
25 songs is a little much, I feel like 4 or 4 songs couldve been dropped from the album. I really only bought this because the last album of his I bought was 2013s Nothing Was The Same. Ive been a fan since Comeback Season and it goes without saying that his earliest work especially So Far Gone, was some of his best. Unfortunately as hes done for the last few albums he falls back on his woes and perceived detractors while outside of a song dedicated to his son he really hasnt shown much maturity or evolution as an artist. Take the track Im Upset for example. Why is he upset? Why? No reason to be but when the market was flooded with releases by Nas, Kanye and Pusha T this album comes in fourth.
